==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[tind]]''. Cognate with German ''[[Zinne]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/taɪn/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[spike]] or point on an implement or tool, especially a [[prong]] of a fork or a [[tooth]] of a comb
# A small branch, especially on an [[antler]] or [[horn]]

